label: Indeterminate sex pubic symphysis morphological stage value specification
definition: A categorical value specification defining an ordinal scale of stages in the degradation of the pubic symphysis in specimens of indeterminate sex.
definition source: Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project: Age-at-Death Estimation Scoring Key, version of 16 September 2022.
referenced category labels: ('has category label' exactly 1 ({phaleron-ae:IndeterminateSexPhase1 , phaleron-ae:IndeterminateSexPhase2, phaleron-ae:IndeterminateSexPhase3, phaleron-ae:IndeterminateSexPhase4, phaleron-ae:IndeterminateSexPhase5, phaleron-ae:IndeterminateSexPhase6 }))

label: Indeterminate sex pubic symphysis morphological stage item sorting
definition: A label sorting specification about the position of a category label within the ordinal scale defined by some 'Indeterminate sex pubic symphysis morphological stage value specification'.
